t6246.text: TL;DR: Guy claimed to be someone else and I didn’t realise for three hours. He said he was my boyfriend and I went along with it. That failed epically.

t6247.text: That lasted three weeks and when it blew up, it blew up spectacularly. I now have him blocked on everything. I haven’t seen him in years because we both finished uni so that’s where the story ends. And that, dear readers, was the worst first date I ever went on.

t6248.text: Old mate thought our conversation had gone really well And he just decided he was my boyfriend. He went around telling everybody that we were dating but there was never any discussion about that. I felt bad and didn’t want to hurt him so I went with it. Biggest. Mistake. Ever.

t6249.text: I’m not sure how we managed to talk for three hours without that coming up but somehow we did. Maybe it’s my fault for not checking more closely that he was Who he claimed to be. Oh but hold on folks, the story does not end there. It gets worse.

t6250.text: I didn’t realise it wasn’t him until I said I thought it was strange that he came back from Melbourne. The real Tristan said he was never coming back. Anyway, this dude said he’d never been there in his life and that’s when I knew it wasn’t him.

t6251.text: This left me with a lot of questions. Who the fuck have I been talking to this entire time? Why was he pretending to be someone else? What on earth did he gain from this?

t6252.text: We started talking and everything was going great. Or so I thought anyway. Turns out, I wasn’t even talking to Tristan at all. This person was just someone Who sounded and acted like him. I didn’t realise until we’ve been talking for three hours.
